-Title- 
Founder of Canadian 'Just for Laughs' comedy festival quits amid abuse allegations
-Keywords-
['allegations', 'abuse', 'montreal', 'weinstein', 'founder', 'quits', 'laughs', 'canadian', 'rozon', 'harassed', 'wake', 'trudeau', 'amid', 'festival', 'comedy', 'women']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
MONTREAL (Reuters) - The founder of Canada’s comedy festival ‘Just for Laughs’, which draws celebrities including Trevor Noah, Sarah Silverman and Jerry Seinfeld, has resigned from his own company in the wake of allegations of sexual harassment.
FILE PHOTO: Gilbert Rozon (L) and Bruce Hills (R) of the television comedy show "Just For Laughs" accept the ICON award during the Canadian Screen Awards in Toronto, Ontario, Canada March 12, 2017.
He is the latest entertainment executive to be accused of sexual harassment in the wake of accusations against U.S. film producer Harvey Weinstein.
