Benchmark 10-year notes US10YT=RR last fell 19/32 in price to yield 2.3899 percent, from 2.321 percent late on Thursday.

The increased risk appetite also sent gold lower. Spot gold XAU= dropped 0.8 percent to $1,279.25 an ounce. U.S. gold futures GCcv1 fell 0.71 percent to $1,280.80 an ounce.

U.S. crude CLcv1 rose 0.19 percent to $51.61 per barrel and Brent LCOcv1 was last at $57.51, up 0.49 percent on the day. Still, oil was set for a weekly loss as investors sought to book profit, despite tensions in the Middle East that have slashed supplies of crude.

(This version of the story updates to U.S. trading, changes dateline to NEW YORK, previous LONDON; refiles to add dropped byline)
