-Title- 
Schlumberger, Baker Hughes warn of weak fourth quarter
-Keywords-
['prices', 'quarter', 'spending', 'north', 'baker', 'estimates', 'oil', 'warn', 'fourth', 'america', 'schlumberger', 'activity', 'energy', 'weak', 'hughes']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
FILE PHOTO: The exterior of the Schlumberger Corporation headquarters building is pictured in the Galleria area of Houston January 16, 2015.
REUTERS/Richard Carson/File PhotoShares of Schlumberger NV (SLB.N) dropped nearly 5 percent to a 21-month low of $61.41, while Baker Hughes (BHGE.N) tumbled 5.2 percent to a 16-month low of $31.44.
