-Title- 
London the starting line as Adidas laces up robotic shoe run
-Keywords-
['starting', 'produce', 'york', 'shoes', 'robots', 'robotic', 'shoe', 'factory', 'adidas', 'plans', 'turneradidas', 'laces', 'run', 'line', 'london']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
LONDON (Reuters) - Adidas has launched the first of six planned city-themed running shoe models in London as it capitalizes on its first Speedfactory, which it has opened in Germany and equipped with time-saving robotics.
A sample AM4LDN shoe is displayed, at the launch of Adidas' new shoe line, made in a factory largely operated by robots, in London, Britain October 19, 2017.
After London it plans shoe models inspired by Paris, New York, Los Angeles, Tokyo and Shanghai.
A staff member displays a shoe, at the launch of Adidas' new shoe line, made in a factory largely operated by robots, in London, Britain October 19, 2017.
