-Title- 
Airbus expects to sell 'thousands' of CSeries jets - CEO
-Keywords-
['airbus', 'jets', 'thousands', 'ceo', 'aircraft', 'aerospace', 'expects', 'cseries', 'trade', 'sell', 'market', 'bombardier', 'venture', 'programme', 'boeing']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
MONTREAL (Reuters) - Airbus (AIR.PA) Chief Executive Tom Enders said on Friday he believed Bombardier Inc’s (BBDb.TO) CSeries planes would capture half the market for smaller single-aisle aircraft with the sale of “thousands” of the 110-to-130 seat jets.
A Bombardier CSeries aircraft is pictured during a news conference to announce a partnership between Airbus and Bombardier on the C Series aircraft programme, in Colomiers near Toulouse, France, October 17, 2017.
On Thursday, the head of a major U.S. airplane leasing company said the deal boosts confidence in the CSeries programme, but is unlikely to drive a flurry of immediate sales.
