-Title- 
Obama blasts 'politics of division' on return to campaign trail
-Keywords-
['division', 'trail', 'obama', 'politics', 'president', 'white', 'blasts', 'return', 'elections', 'republican', 'house', 'jersey', 'virginia', 'campaign', 'trump']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
(Reuters) - Former President Barack Obama, back on the campaign trail on Thursday for the first time since he left the White House, called on voters to reject a growing “politics of division” that he said was corroding American democracy.
“It’s the 21st century, not the 19th century.”At a later stop in Richmond, Virginia, Obama said modern politics increasingly did not reflect basic American values of inclusiveness and were driving people away from the process.
