-Title- 
Microsoft expands rural U.S. campaign with Green Bay Packers tie-up
-Keywords-
['tieup', 'rural', 'partnership', 'tech', 'packers', 'facebook', 'green', 'million', 'billion', 'states', 'expands', 'bay', 'smith', 'microsoft', 'campaign']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp (MSFT.O) has teamed up with the National Football League’s Green Bay Packers in a $10 million partnership intended to spur tech innovation in Wisconsin, the software company said on Thursday.
”We’re much more likely to find it in Green Bay, Wisconsin.”Through the partnership, known as TitletownTech, the Packers and Microsoft will each contribute $5 million to invest in startups from around Wisconsin.
